<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Purse1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Purse,</orth> subst. a small money-bag carried in the pocket: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.357" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 357</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.181" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 181</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.198" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 105</bibl> <cit><quote>(a p. of ducats).</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 29</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.4.90" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 90</bibl> <cit><quote>(a p. of ducats).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 16</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.5.51" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 4, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.173" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 173</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.7.14" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 7, 14</bibl> <cit><quote>(this p. of gold).</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.5.46" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 46</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.303" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 303</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 127</bibl> <cit><quote>(your p. is not hot enough).</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 61</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.142" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 142</bibl> <cit><quote>(fat --s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.355" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 355</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>(cold --s).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 1, 34</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>(a friend i' the court is better than a penny in p.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 10</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.37" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.131" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.131" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 131</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.516" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 516</bibl> etc. etc. <cit><quote>she bears the p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 76</bibl></cit>; cf. <cit><quote>hast had my p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 2</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>nor will he know his p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 200</bibl></cit> (the state of his finances). <cit><quote>a halfpenny p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.149" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou halfpenny p. of wit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 77</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>